physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Physical examination showed no abnormalities. Neurologic examination revealed nystagmus, cerebellar ataxia of upper and lower limbs, pyramidal tract signs more pronounced in the lower limbs causing a spastic-ataxic gait, marked defect in proprioception and pallesthesia, and mildly decreased muscle strength in the distal muscles of the lower limbs symmetrically. Symmetrical atrophy of the intrinsic foot muscles was noted. Ophthalmological and cardiological assessment showed no abnormalities.
